    <id>org.coolero.Coolero</id>
    <name>Coolero</name>
    <summary>Coolero is a program to monitor and control your cooling devices</summary>
    <developer_name>codifryed</developer_name>
    <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
    <project_license>GPL-3.0</project_license>

    <url type="homepage">https://gitlab.com/codifryed/coolero</url>
    <url type="bugtracker">https://gitlab.com/codifryed/coolero/-/issues</url>

    <description>
        <p>
            Monitor and control various liquid cooling and other devices like the NZXT Kraken, Corsair Commander, and
            others.
        </p>
        <p>
            It offers an easy-to-use user interface with various control features and also provides live thermal
            performance details.
        </p>
        <p>
            Coolero is a frontend and enhancement for Liquidctl, which actually talks to the devices, in addition to
            other libraries.
        </p>
    </description>
